cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO

This paper discusses the use of Neuroevolution, a subfield of machine learning, to solve reinforcement learning tasks. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of surrogate models, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization, leading to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves the optimization of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of reinforcement learning suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of phenotypic distance measures, which are commonly used in robotics, leading to cs.RO (Robotics) as a possible sub-category.
